Arrays are used to hold a fixed number of values of a single data type

The code for an int array is 
int[] intArray = new int [3];
intArray[0] = 1;
intArray[1] = 2;
intArray[2] = 3;
The code for a String array is 
String value = grassMap.getTileProperty(tileID, "blocked", "false");
String [] donuts = {"maple","bismark","berliner"}

The code for a boolean array is 
Blocked.blocked = new boolean [grassMap.getWidth()][grassMap.getHeight()];

The code for a double array is
double [] marble = {".65355", ".5512"}

You would change the first value of the int array to 42 by changing the 
fixed value to intArray[0] = 42;


