The code private String[] dessert = new String[3]; calls the 3rd sequence in 
the string

The code private String[] postres = {"rice pudding", "pan dulce", "bunelos"}
sets up the sequences of the String

The two codes are different because one is setting up which String will be
printed and the other is setting up the strings in order of being printed

